.TH "ir_timer_repeat" 9 "ir_timer_repeat" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ir_timer_repeat \- generates a repeat event after a timeout
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" ir_timer_repeat
.BI "(struct timer_list *t "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "t" 12
a pointer to the struct timer_list
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This routine will generate a soft repeat event every REP_PERIOD
milliseconds.
